WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.578 --> 00:00:16.320
I'm going to first tell you something that in my grandmother
我打算先告诉你们一件事， 就连我祖母

2
00:00:16.344 --> 00:00:19.081
would've elicited a five-oy alarm:
听了都会发出五声哎唷，

3
00:00:19.106 --> 00:00:20.368
"Oy-oy-oy-oy-oy."
” 哎唷哎唷哎唷哎唷哎唷。“

4
00:00:20.392 --> 00:00:21.542
(Laughter)
（笑声）

5
00:00:21.566 --> 00:00:24.851
And here it is ... are you ready?
事情是这样的...你们准备好了吗？

6
00:00:25.342 --> 00:00:26.492
OK.
好的。

7
00:00:27.550 --> 00:00:31.286
I have stage IV lung cancer.
我得了晚期的肺癌。

8
00:00:32.089 --> 00:00:33.391
Oh, I know, "poor me."
噢，我知道，" 我真可怜。”

9
00:00:33.415 --> 00:00:34.657
I don't feel that way.
我并不这么认为。

10
00:00:34.681 --> 00:00:36.732
I'm so OK with it.
我觉得根本没什么。

11
00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:39.339
And granted, I have certain advantages --
老实说，我还有一些好处--

12
00:00:39.363 --> 00:00:42.020
not everybody can take so cavalier an attitude.
不是每个人都能抱着这么无忧无虑的心态。

13
00:00:42.044 --> 00:00:43.568
I don't have young children.
我没有年幼的孩子要抚养。

14
00:00:44.175 --> 00:00:47.863
I have a grown daughter who's brilliant and happy and wonderful.
我有一个成年的，聪明，快乐，棒极了的女儿。

15
00:00:48.494 --> 00:00:51.516
I don't have huge financial stress.
我没有巨大的财务压力。

16
00:00:52.531 --> 00:00:54.541
My cancer isn't that aggressive.
我的癌症也没那么来势汹汹。

17
00:00:54.565 --> 00:00:56.785
It's kind of like the Democratic leadership --
它倒有点像民主党的领导风格。

18
00:00:56.809 --> 00:01:00.492
(Laughter)
（笑声）

19
00:01:00.516 --> 00:01:02.382
not convinced it can win.
不让人信服它会赢。

20
00:01:02.406 --> 00:01:04.056
It's basically just sitting there,
基本上只是坐在那里，

21
00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:06.416
waiting for Goldman Sachs to give it some money.
等着高盛集团给点钱。

22
00:01:06.440 --> 00:01:07.455
(Laughter)
（笑声）

23
00:01:07.479 --> 00:01:12.368
(Applause)
（掌声）

24
00:01:12.392 --> 00:01:15.225
Oh, and the best thing of all --
噢，最棒的事情是

25
00:01:15.249 --> 00:01:18.717
I have a major accomplishment under my belt.
我获得了一个很大的成就。

26
00:01:18.741 --> 00:01:19.892
Yes.
没错。

27
00:01:19.916 --> 00:01:23.820
I didn't even know it until someone tweeted me a year ago.
要不是有人一年前在推特上给我发了条信息， 我甚至都不记得了。

28
00:01:23.844 --> 00:01:26.066
And here's what they said:
他们是这么说的：

29
00:01:26.090 --> 00:01:28.311
"You are responsible
"你要对那些

30
00:01:28.335 --> 00:01:31.394
for the pussification of the American male."
没种的美国男性们负责。"

31
00:01:31.859 --> 00:01:33.689
(Laughter)
（笑声）

32
00:01:33.713 --> 00:01:37.564
(Applause)
（掌声）

33
00:01:37.588 --> 00:01:40.390
Not that I can take all the credit, but ...
我并不想把功劳都归到我身上，但是...

34
00:01:40.414 --> 00:01:44.652
(Laughter)
（笑声）

35
00:01:44.676 --> 00:01:48.605
But what if you don't have my advantages?
但是你们要是没有我这些优势呢？

36
00:01:48.629 --> 00:01:52.303
The only advice I can give you is to do what I did:
我能给的唯一建议就是按照我做的去做：

37
00:01:52.327 --> 00:01:55.023
make friends with reality.
和现实交朋友。

38
00:01:55.454 --> 00:01:59.226
You couldn't have a worse relationship with reality than I did.
你们不可能有比我与现实更糟的关系了。

39
00:01:59.823 --> 00:02:02.311
From the get-go,
从一开始，

40
00:02:02.335 --> 00:02:04.657
I wasn't even attracted to reality.
我甚至都不被现实所吸引。

41
00:02:05.196 --> 00:02:07.903
If they'd had Tinder when I met reality,
如果我在Tinder（交友软件）上遇见现实时，

42
00:02:07.927 --> 00:02:09.117
I would have swiped left
我肯定左划（表示不喜欢）

43
00:02:09.141 --> 00:02:11.134
and the whole thing would have been over.
然后就没有然后了。

44
00:02:11.158 --> 00:02:12.824
(Laughter)
（笑声）

45
00:02:12.848 --> 00:02:14.837
And reality and I --
并且现实和我——

46
00:02:14.861 --> 00:02:18.256
we don't share the same values, the same goals --
我们没有相同的价值观，相同的目标——

47
00:02:18.280 --> 00:02:19.287
(Laughter)
（笑声）

48
00:02:19.311 --> 00:02:22.010
To be honest, I don't have goals;
老实说，我没有目标；

49
00:02:22.034 --> 00:02:23.635
I have fantasies.
我有幻想。

50
00:02:24.208 --> 00:02:27.898
They're exactly like goals but without the hard work.
它们和目标很像，只是不需要任何努力。

51
00:02:27.922 --> 00:02:29.872
(Laughter)
（笑声）

52
00:02:29.896 --> 00:02:31.325
(Applause)
（掌声）

53
00:02:31.349 --> 00:02:34.595
I'm not a big fan of hard work,
我不是工作狂，

54
00:02:34.619 --> 00:02:36.517
but you know reality --
但你们了解现实——

55
00:02:36.541 --> 00:02:39.510
it's either push, push, push, push, push
它要么就是逼迫，逼迫，逼迫，逼迫，逼迫，

56
00:02:39.534 --> 00:02:43.847
through its agent, the executive brain function --
通过它的中间人，大脑执行功能——

57
00:02:43.871 --> 00:02:45.416
one of the "yays" of dying:
其中一个渴望欢呼“哇”：

58
00:02:45.440 --> 00:02:49.063
my executive brain function won't have me to kick around anymore.
我的大脑执行功能不再让我有更多考虑。

59
00:02:49.087 --> 00:02:53.133
(Laughter)
(笑声)

60
00:02:53.157 --> 00:02:56.462
But something happened
但一些事情就这样发生了,

61
00:02:56.486 --> 00:03:00.691
that made me realize
它让我意识到，

62
00:03:00.715 --> 00:03:05.049
that reality may not be reality.
现实可能不是真实。

63
00:03:05.386 --> 00:03:06.908
So what happened was,
所以发生的是，

64
00:03:06.932 --> 00:03:11.392
because I basically wanted reality to leave me alone --
因为我主要想让现实离我远一点——

65
00:03:11.416 --> 00:03:14.409
but I wanted to be left alone in a nice house
但我想一个人待在漂亮的大房子里，

66
00:03:14.433 --> 00:03:18.199
with a Wolf range and Sub-Zero refrigerator ...
房子里有一个Wolf牌子的灶具和 Sub-Zero牌子的电冰箱...

67
00:03:18.223 --> 00:03:20.574
private yoga lessons --
私人的瑜伽课程——

68
00:03:20.598 --> 00:03:24.323
I ended up with a development deal at Disney.
最终我和迪士尼达成了一个开发协议。

69
00:03:24.347 --> 00:03:27.806
And one day I found myself in my new office
然后有一天，我在自己矮人路上的

70
00:03:27.830 --> 00:03:30.145
on Two Dopey Drive --
新办公室里（迪士尼总部所在地）——

71
00:03:30.169 --> 00:03:33.159
(Laughter)
(笑声)

72
00:03:33.183 --> 00:03:36.263
which reality thought I should be proud of ...
现实原以为我应当很自豪...

73
00:03:36.287 --> 00:03:37.437
(Laughter)
（笑声）

74
00:03:37.461 --> 00:03:41.867
And I'm staring at the present they sent me to celebrate my arrival --
然后我看着他们寄来的庆祝我到来的礼物...

75
00:03:41.891 --> 00:03:46.985
not the Lalique vase or the grand piano I've heard of other people getting,
不是Lalique（法国知名水晶品牌）的花瓶， 或者是我听说其他人得到的大钢琴，

76
00:03:47.009 --> 00:03:50.366
but a three-foot-tall, stuffed Mickey Mouse
而是三英尺高的毛绒米老鼠

77
00:03:50.390 --> 00:03:51.405
(Laughter)
（笑声）

78
00:03:51.429 --> 00:03:54.287
with a catalog, in case I wanted to order some more stuff
和一份产品目录，以防我想要订购更多的东西，

79
00:03:54.311 --> 00:03:56.315
that didn't jibe with my aesthetic.
但那并没有骗过我的审美。

80
00:03:56.339 --> 00:03:57.376
(Laughter)
(笑声)

81
00:03:57.400 --> 00:03:59.146
And when I looked up in the catalog
然后当我翻了翻目录册,

82
00:03:59.170 --> 00:04:03.528
to see how much this three-foot-high mouse cost,
想看看这三英尺高的米老鼠多少钱，

83
00:04:03.552 --> 00:04:06.376
here's how it was described ...
它是这么描述的...

84
00:04:07.423 --> 00:04:09.751
"Life-sized."
“ 真人大小。”

85
00:04:09.775 --> 00:04:14.613
(Laughter)
（笑声）

86
00:04:14.637 --> 00:04:16.296
And that's when I knew.
就在这一刻我知道了。

87
00:04:16.698 --> 00:04:19.093
Reality wasn't "reality."
现实并不是“ 真实。”

88
00:04:19.117 --> 00:04:21.075
Reality was an imposter.
现实是个骗子。

89
00:04:21.757 --> 00:04:26.258
So I dived into quantum physics and chaos theory
因此我埋头苦读量子物理学和混沌理论，

90
00:04:26.282 --> 00:04:28.428
to try to find actual reality,
试图找到真实的现实，

91
00:04:28.452 --> 00:04:30.097
and I've just finished a movie --
然后我就完成了一部电影——

92
00:04:30.121 --> 00:04:32.321
yes, finally finished --
是的，最终完成了——

93
00:04:32.345 --> 00:04:33.523
about all that,
关于那一切的，

94
00:04:33.547 --> 00:04:34.852
so I won't go into it here,
因此我就不在这儿细聊了，

95
00:04:34.876 --> 00:04:37.342
and anyway, it wasn't until after we shot the movie,
总之，直到我们把电影拍出来，它才成型，

96
00:04:37.366 --> 00:04:39.428
when I broke my leg and then it didn't heal,
那时我摔断了我的腿，还没痊愈，

97
00:04:39.452 --> 00:04:41.893
so then they had to do another surgery a year later,
需要一年后再做一个手术，

98
00:04:41.917 --> 00:04:43.288
and then that took a year --
然后又花了一年时间——

99
00:04:42.862 --> 00:04:44.553
two years in a wheelchair,
两年间我坐在轮椅上，

100
00:04:44.593 --> 00:04:50.543
and that's when I came into contact with actual reality:
就在那时，我实实在在地与现实发生了联系：

101
00:04:50.567 --> 00:04:51.932
limits.
限制。

102
00:04:52.418 --> 00:04:55.448
Those very limits I'd spent my whole life denying
那些我花了一生时间否认，

103
00:04:55.472 --> 00:04:57.785
and pushing past and ignoring
绕开并不予理睬的限制

104
00:04:59.286 --> 00:05:00.853
were real,
是真实的，

105
00:05:00.877 --> 00:05:03.214
and I had to deal with them,
并且我不得不去面对它们，

106
00:05:03.238 --> 00:05:08.929
and they took imagination, creativity and my entire skill set.
我耗尽了我的想象力，创造力以及所有技能。

107
00:05:09.281 --> 00:05:13.662
It turned out I was great at actual reality.
结果证明我很擅长处理实实在在的现实。

108
00:05:14.109 --> 00:05:15.824
I didn't just come to terms with it,
我不仅仅和它达成了妥协，

109
00:05:15.848 --> 00:05:17.442
I fell in love.
我还爱上了它。

110
00:05:17.466 --> 00:05:18.927
And I should've known,
并且我本该已经知道，

111
00:05:18.951 --> 00:05:22.933
given my equally shaky relationship with the zeitgeist ...
给予时代精神一个同样不坚定的关系...

112
00:05:23.987 --> 00:05:28.183
I'll just say, if anyone is in the market for a Betamax --
我将只会说，如果有谁想买一个 Betamax（Beta制录像系统）——

113
00:05:28.207 --> 00:05:30.201
(Laughter)
(笑声)

114
00:05:30.604 --> 00:05:34.452
I should have known that the moment I fell in love with reality,
我本该已经知道当我爱上现实的那一刻，

115
00:05:34.476 --> 00:05:37.759
the rest of the country would decide to go in the opposite direction.
这个国家的其他人都会决定朝着相反的方向走。

116
00:05:37.783 --> 00:05:40.092
(Laughter)
（笑声）

117
00:05:40.116 --> 00:05:44.661
But I'm not here to talk about Trump or the alt-right or climate-change deniers
但我不是在这儿讨论特朗普或是另类右派， 又或是气候变化的否认派们，

118
00:05:44.685 --> 00:05:47.075
or even the makers of this thing,
甚至是这件事的制造者，

119
00:05:47.099 --> 00:05:48.965
which I would have called a box,
就像我会叫这个东西是一个盒子，

120
00:05:48.989 --> 00:05:51.874
except that right here, it says,
除了在这右边，写着，

121
00:05:51.898 --> 00:05:54.585
"This is not a box."
“ 这不是一个盒子。”

122
00:05:54.609 --> 00:05:59.125
(Laughter)
（笑声）

123
00:05:59.149 --> 00:06:01.287
They're gaslighting me.
他们正在蒙骗我。

124
00:06:01.311 --> 00:06:02.973
(Laughter)
（笑声）

125
00:06:02.997 --> 00:06:05.633
(Applause)
（掌声）

126
00:06:06.521 --> 00:06:11.252
But what I do want to talk about
但我确实想讨论的

127
00:06:11.276 --> 00:06:16.394
is a personal challenge to reality
是一个我对于现实的个人挑战，

128
00:06:16.418 --> 00:06:19.065
that I take personally,
针对我自己的，

129
00:06:19.089 --> 00:06:25.766
and I want to preface it by saying that I absolutely love science.
并且我想先声明我是绝对热爱科学的。

130
00:06:26.136 --> 00:06:27.517
I have this --
我拥有这个——

131
00:06:27.541 --> 00:06:29.505
not a scientist myself --
不是一个科学家的我——

132
00:06:29.529 --> 00:06:34.347
but an uncanny ability to understand everything about science,
而是一种理解所有关于科学的神秘能力，

133
00:06:34.371 --> 00:06:36.254
except the actual science --
不包括实实在在的科学——

134
00:06:36.278 --> 00:06:37.279
(Laughter)
（笑声）

135
00:06:37.303 --> 00:06:38.501
which is math.
也就是数学。

136
00:06:38.525 --> 00:06:42.800
But the most outlandish concepts make sense to me.
但我能理解最奇特的概念。

137
00:06:44.788 --> 00:06:46.177
The string theory;
弦理论；

138
00:06:46.201 --> 00:06:50.369
the idea that all of reality emanates from the vibrations of these teeny --
它的想法是所有的现实是 从这些微小的振动中散发出来的——

139
00:06:50.393 --> 00:06:52.305
I call it "The Big Twang."
我称之为“ 一个大大的拨弦声。”

140
00:06:52.329 --> 00:06:53.588
(Laughter)
（笑声）

141
00:06:54.225 --> 00:06:56.222
Wave-particle duality:
波粒二象性：

142
00:06:56.246 --> 00:06:59.887
the idea that one thing can manifest as two things ...
这个理论是一件东西能够以两件事物来显示...

143
00:06:59.911 --> 00:07:01.062
you know?
你们知道吗？

144
00:07:01.086 --> 00:07:04.908
That a photon can manifest as a wave and a particle
光子能够以波和粒子来显示，

145
00:07:04.932 --> 00:07:07.293
coincided with my deepest intuitions
恰好和我心底的直觉不谋而合，

146
00:07:07.317 --> 00:07:09.000
that people are good and bad,
人类有好有坏，

147
00:07:09.024 --> 00:07:11.114
ideas are right and wrong.
想法有对有错。

148
00:07:11.138 --> 00:07:13.418
Freud was right about penis envy
佛洛伊德曾对于 阴茎羡慕心理的理论是对的，

149
00:07:13.442 --> 00:07:16.022
and he was wrong about who has it.
同时他对于谁有这样的心理是错的。

150
00:07:16.046 --> 00:07:19.635
(Laughter)
（笑声）

151
00:07:19.659 --> 00:07:22.183
(Applause)
（掌声）

152
00:07:22.207 --> 00:07:23.450
Thank you.
谢谢。

153
00:07:23.474 --> 00:07:24.481
(Applause)
（掌声）

154
00:07:24.505 --> 00:07:27.896
And then there's this slight variation on that,
那儿有微小的差别，

155
00:07:27.920 --> 00:07:30.603
which is reality looks like two things,
现实看起来像两样东西，

156
00:07:30.627 --> 00:07:34.785
but it turns out to be the interaction of those two things,
但其实是两者之间的一种相互作用，

157
00:07:34.809 --> 00:07:36.957
like space -- time,
就像空间——时间，

158
00:07:36.981 --> 00:07:38.622
mass -- energy
数量——能量

159
00:07:38.646 --> 00:07:41.896
and life and death.
以及生命和死亡。

160
00:07:42.264 --> 00:07:43.793
So I don't understand --
因此我不明白——

161
00:07:43.817 --> 00:07:46.887
I simply just don't understand
就是不明白，

162
00:07:46.911 --> 00:07:51.276
the mindset of people who are out to "defeat death" and "overcome death."
那些有着想要跳出来 “打败死亡”和“攻克死亡”心态的人，

163
00:07:51.300 --> 00:07:52.892
How do you do that?
你们如何做到？

164
00:07:52.916 --> 00:07:55.752
How do you defeat death without killing off life?
你们如何在不结束生命的情况下打败死亡？

165
00:07:56.359 --> 00:07:58.574
It doesn't make sense to me.
这对我来说讲不通。

166
00:07:58.598 --> 00:08:00.530
I also have to say,
我也不得不说，

167
00:08:00.554 --> 00:08:04.322
I find it incredibly ungrateful.
我觉得这相当忘恩负义。

168
00:08:04.346 --> 00:08:07.111
I mean, you're given this extraordinary gift --
我的意思是你拥有这一件很特别的礼物——

169
00:08:07.135 --> 00:08:08.521
life --
生命——

170
00:08:08.545 --> 00:08:13.203
but it's as if you had asked Santa for a Rolls-Royce Silver Shadow
但这就好像你已经 向圣诞老人要了劳斯莱斯银影汽车，

171
00:08:13.227 --> 00:08:15.939
and you had gotten a salad spinner instead.
然后你却得到了沙拉脱水器。

172
00:08:16.492 --> 00:08:18.840
You know, it's the beef --
你知道的，牛肉——

173
00:08:18.864 --> 00:08:22.685
the beef with it is that it comes with an expiration date.
牛肉有它的保质期。

174
00:08:22.709 --> 00:08:24.503
Death is the deal breaker.
死亡是一场血色交易。

175
00:08:25.774 --> 00:08:26.925
I don't get that.
我不理解。

176
00:08:26.949 --> 00:08:28.100
I don't understand --
我不明白——

177
00:08:28.124 --> 00:08:29.768
to me, it's disrespectful.
对我来说，那是不尊重的。

178
00:08:29.792 --> 00:08:31.675
It's disrespectful to nature.
对大自然的不尊重。

179
00:08:32.224 --> 00:08:34.697
The idea that we're going to dominate nature,
那种我们要主导大自然，

180
00:08:34.721 --> 00:08:36.903
we're going to master nature,
我们要掌控大自然的想法，

181
00:08:36.927 --> 00:08:40.807
nature is too weak to withstand our intellect --
大自然太无力而 不能抵抗我们这些高智商的人群——

182
00:08:41.704 --> 00:08:44.500
no, I don't think so.
不，我不这么认为。

183
00:08:44.875 --> 00:08:48.295
I think if you've actually read quantum physics as I have --
我想你们实际上正如我一样 已经读过量子物理学——

184
00:08:48.319 --> 00:08:51.191
well, I read an email from someone who'd read it, but --
嗯，我读了一封来自 一位已经读过量子物理学人的邮件，但是——

185
00:08:51.215 --> 00:08:55.088
(Laughter)
（笑声）

186
00:08:55.112 --> 00:08:56.359
You have to understand
你得明白，

187
00:08:56.383 --> 00:09:00.216
that we don't live in Newton's clockwork universe anymore.
我们不再生活在牛顿的发条宇宙。

188
00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:03.445
We live in a banana peel universe,
我们生活在一个香蕉皮宇宙，

189
00:09:03.469 --> 00:09:07.149
and we won't ever be able to know everything
并且我们不再能知道一切，

190
00:09:07.173 --> 00:09:08.819
or control everything
或者控制一切，

191
00:09:08.843 --> 00:09:10.326
or predict everything.
或者预测一切。

192
00:09:10.350 --> 00:09:12.557
Nature is like a self-driving car.
大自然就像一辆自动驾驶的汽车。

193
00:09:12.581 --> 00:09:15.914
The best we can be is like the old woman in that joke --
我们能做的最好的就像是那位笑话里的老妇人——

194
00:09:15.938 --> 00:09:17.760
I don't know if you've heard it.
我不知道你们有没有听过。

195
00:09:18.072 --> 00:09:20.395
An old woman is driving
一位老妇人正在开车，

196
00:09:20.419 --> 00:09:24.648
with her middle-aged daughter in the passenger seat,
副驾驶坐着她中年的女儿，

197
00:09:24.672 --> 00:09:27.071
and the mother goes right through a red light.
母亲在红灯时直接闯过去了。

198
00:09:27.095 --> 00:09:31.271
And the daughter doesn't want to say anything that makes it sound like,
女儿不想说出任何听起来好像是，

199
00:09:31.295 --> 00:09:32.989
"You're too old to drive,"
“你年纪太大不能开车了,” 这样的话，

200
00:09:33.013 --> 00:09:34.824
so she didn't say anything.
所以她什么也没说。

201
00:09:34.848 --> 00:09:37.572
And then the mother goes through a second red light,
然后这位母亲在第二处红灯时又闯过去了，

202
00:09:37.596 --> 00:09:39.970
and the daughter, as tactfully as possible,
女儿尽可能机智地

203
00:09:39.994 --> 00:09:42.149
says, "Mom, are you aware
说：“妈妈，你有没有意识到

204
00:09:42.173 --> 00:09:44.411
that you just went through two red lights?"
你刚刚闯过两个红灯？"

205
00:09:44.435 --> 00:09:46.430
And the mother says, "Oh, am I driving?"
母亲说，“噢，我正在开车吗？”

206
00:09:46.454 --> 00:09:50.635
(Laughter)
（笑声）

207
00:09:50.659 --> 00:09:55.023
(Applause)
（掌声）

208
00:09:54.999 --> 00:09:56.356
So ...
所以...

209
00:09:57.824 --> 00:10:01.976
and now, I'm going to take a mental leap,
现在，我思维要跳跃一下，

210
00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:05.889
which is easy for me because I'm the Evel Knievel of mental leaps;
这对我来说很容易， 因为我是思维跳跃上的Evel Knievel（特级演员）

211
00:10:05.913 --> 00:10:07.708
my license plate says,
我的车牌写着，

212
00:10:07.732 --> 00:10:10.372
"Cogito, ergo zoom."
“我思，故我快。”

213
00:10:10.892 --> 00:10:14.259
I hope you're willing to come with me on this,
我希望你们跟得上我，

214
00:10:14.283 --> 00:10:19.903
but my real problem with the mindset that is so out to defeat death
但我对于那种试图打败死亡思想的不认同，

215
00:10:19.927 --> 00:10:23.687
is if you're anti-death,
在于你是否是在对抗死亡，

216
00:10:23.711 --> 00:10:26.108
which to me translates as anti-life,
这对我而言就等于是对抗生命，

217
00:10:26.132 --> 00:10:29.993
which to me translates as anti-nature,
对我来说就是对抗大自然，

218
00:10:30.017 --> 00:10:33.148
it also translates to me as anti-woman,
那对我来说也是对抗女性，

219
00:10:33.172 --> 00:10:37.478
because women have long been identified with nature.
因为女性长久以来已经等同于大自然。

220
00:10:37.502 --> 00:10:39.744
And my source on this is Hannah Arendt,
并且我的资料来源于Hannah Arendt,

221
00:10:39.768 --> 00:10:43.395
the German philosopher who wrote a book called "The Human Condition."
一位德国哲学家，写过一本书叫做“人类境况”。

222
00:10:43.990 --> 00:10:47.429
And in it, she says that classically,
在书中，她提到，传统上来说，

223
00:10:47.453 --> 00:10:50.119
work is associated with men.
男人跟工作紧密相连，

224
00:10:50.143 --> 00:10:52.353
Work is what comes out of the head;
工作是一个从大脑冒出来的东西，

225
00:10:52.377 --> 00:10:53.653
it's what we invent,
是我们发明出来的，

226
00:10:53.677 --> 00:10:55.208
it's what we create,
是我们创造出来的，

227
00:10:55.232 --> 00:10:57.872
it's how we leave our mark upon the world.
是我们如何在这个世界上留下我们印记。

228
00:10:59.254 --> 00:11:03.696
Whereas labor is associated with the body.
然而， 劳动是和我们身体联系在一起。

229
00:11:03.720 --> 00:11:06.511
It's associated with the people who perform labor
是和完成工作

230
00:11:06.535 --> 00:11:08.163
or undergo labor.
或是正在工作的人类联系在一起。

231
00:11:08.735 --> 00:11:11.458
So to me,
所以对我来说，

232
00:11:11.482 --> 00:11:15.610
the mindset that denies that,
这种思维模式，

233
00:11:14.918 --> 00:11:19.971
that denies that we're in sync with the biorhythms,
这种否认我们与生物周期一致的思维模式，

234
00:11:19.971 --> 00:11:23.058
the cyclical rhythms of the universe,
否认宇宙的周期性节奏的思维模式，

235
00:11:23.082 --> 00:11:28.736
does not create a hospitable environment for women
并没有为女性

236
00:11:27.420 --> 00:11:31.178
or for people associated with labor,
或是工作的人类创造出舒适的环境，

237
00:11:31.218 --> 00:11:32.732
which is to say,
所以要说，

238
00:11:32.756 --> 00:11:36.175
people that we associate as descendants of slaves,
人类成为了奴隶的后代，

239
00:11:36.199 --> 00:11:38.546
or people who perform manual labor.
或是那些进行手工劳作的人们。

240
00:11:39.658 --> 00:11:45.372
So here's how it looks from a banana-peel-universe point of view,
所以，从香蕉皮宇宙的角度来看看它是怎样的，

241
00:11:45.396 --> 00:11:48.731
from my mindset, which I call "Emily's universe."
从我的思维概念来说，我叫它“艾米莉的宇宙。”

242
00:11:49.628 --> 00:11:50.803
First of all,
首先，

243
00:11:52.143 --> 00:11:57.388
I am incredibly grateful for life,
我非常地感激生活，

244
00:11:57.412 --> 00:11:59.479
but I don't want to be immortal.
但我并不想不朽。

245
00:11:59.952 --> 00:12:03.970
I have no interest in having my name live on after me.
我对千古留名并没兴趣。

246
00:12:03.994 --> 00:12:06.173
In fact, I don't want it to,
实际上，我也不想这样，

247
00:12:06.197 --> 00:12:07.851
because it's been my observation
因为据我观察，

248
00:12:07.875 --> 00:12:10.600
that no matter how nice and how brilliant
无论你人多好，多聪明

249
00:12:10.624 --> 00:12:12.236
or how talented you are,
或是多有才华，

250
00:12:12.260 --> 00:12:14.872
50 years after you die, they turn on you.
在你死后50年， 他们会对你进行攻击。

251
00:12:14.896 --> 00:12:16.372
(Laughter)
（笑声）

252
00:12:16.396 --> 00:12:18.911
And I have actual proof of that.
并且我实际的证据，

253
00:12:18.935 --> 00:12:22.167
A headline from the Los Angeles Times:
一则来自洛杉矶时报的大标题：

254
00:12:22.191 --> 00:12:25.322
"Anne Frank: Not so nice after all."
"安妮·弗兰克（二战犹太人大屠杀中最著名的 受害者之一）： 归根到底并没有那么好。"

255
00:12:25.346 --> 00:12:30.616
(Laughter)
（笑声）

256
00:12:30.640 --> 00:12:34.002
Plus, I love being in sync
此外，我热爱

257
00:12:34.026 --> 00:12:36.545
with the cyclical rhythms of the universe.
与宇宙的周期性节奏保持一致。

258
00:12:36.569 --> 00:12:38.838
That's what's so extraordinary about life:
那是对生命多么特别的事情，

259
00:12:38.862 --> 00:12:41.059
it's a cycle of generation,
这是新生的循环，

260
00:12:41.083 --> 00:12:42.489
degeneration,
退化的，

261
00:12:42.513 --> 00:12:44.112
regeneration.
再生的周期。

262
00:12:44.136 --> 00:12:48.034
"I" am just a collection of particles
“我”只是众多颗粒的集合，

263
00:12:48.058 --> 00:12:50.937
that is arranged into this pattern,
这些颗粒被排列出这种模式，

264
00:12:50.961 --> 00:12:53.723
then will decompose and be available,
然后分解，再变的可用，

265
00:12:53.747 --> 00:12:56.294
all of its constituent parts, to nature,
所有这些组成部分，对大自然而言，

266
00:12:56.318 --> 00:12:58.472
to reorganize into another pattern.
重组成另一种模式。

267
00:12:59.599 --> 00:13:02.058
To me, that is so exciting,
对我来说是无比令人兴奋的，

268
00:13:02.082 --> 00:13:06.490
and it makes me even more grateful to be part of that process.
这使我对我成为这个过程的一部分而更加感激。

269
00:13:07.151 --> 00:13:08.871
You know,
你们知道吗，

270
00:13:08.895 --> 00:13:14.937
I look at death now from the point of view of a German biologist,
我现在以德国生物学家，

271
00:13:14.961 --> 00:13:16.416
Andreas Weber,
Andreas Weber的角度看待死亡。

272
00:13:16.440 --> 00:13:20.042
who looks at it as part of the gift economy.
他把死亡看作是礼物经济的一部分。

273
00:13:20.066 --> 00:13:22.844
You're given this enormous gift, life,
你被给予了巨大的礼物——生命，

274
00:13:22.868 --> 00:13:25.211
you enrich it as best you can,
你尽最大努力地丰富它，

275
00:13:25.235 --> 00:13:27.295
and then you give it back.
然后你将它归还。

276
00:13:27.839 --> 00:13:31.172
And, you know, Auntie Mame said, "Life is a banquet" --
同时，你知道吗， Auntie Mame 说过: “生命是一场盛宴” ——

277
00:13:31.196 --> 00:13:33.307
well, I've eaten my fill.
嗯，我已经尽情地享用了美食。

278
00:13:33.946 --> 00:13:36.217
I have had an enormous appetite for life,
我已经对生活充满了期望，

279
00:13:36.241 --> 00:13:37.464
I've consumed life,
我享受了生命，

280
00:13:37.488 --> 00:13:40.123
but in death, I'm going to be consumed.
但在死亡里，我将被享用。

281
00:13:40.147 --> 00:13:43.598
I'm going into the ground just the way I am,
我将以我原本的样子入土为安，

282
00:13:43.622 --> 00:13:46.573
and there, I invite every microbe
在那儿，我邀请每一个细菌，

283
00:13:46.597 --> 00:13:47.953
and detritus-er
碎石，

284
00:13:47.977 --> 00:13:50.127
and decomposer
分解者，

285
00:13:50.151 --> 00:13:51.317
to have their fill.
去享用我——

286
00:13:51.341 --> 00:13:53.897
I think they'll find me delicious.
我认为它们会发现我的美味。

287
00:13:53.921 --> 00:13:55.123
(Laughter)
（笑声）

288
00:13:55.147 --> 00:13:56.397
I do.
我确实这么认为。

289
00:13:57.404 --> 00:14:02.443
So the best thing about my attitude, I think, is that it's real.
所以关于我态度最棒的事情， 我认为这一切是真实的。

290
00:14:02.467 --> 00:14:03.793
You can see it.
你能看见它。

291
00:14:03.817 --> 00:14:04.968
You can observe it.
你能观察它。

292
00:14:04.992 --> 00:14:06.458
It actually happens.
它实实在在地发生着。

293
00:14:06.482 --> 00:14:10.197
Well, maybe not my enriching the gift,
嗯，可能没有丰富的礼物，

294
00:14:10.221 --> 00:14:11.976
I don't know about that --
我不知道——

295
00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:15.568
but my life has certainly been enriched by other people.
但我的生命确实已经被其他朋友所丰富着。

296
00:14:15.592 --> 00:14:16.797
By TED,
被TED，

297
00:14:16.821 --> 00:14:19.980
which introduced me to a whole network of people
它介绍我认识了一群朋友，

298
00:14:20.004 --> 00:14:22.683
who have enriched my life,
他们使我生活丰富多彩，

299
00:14:22.707 --> 00:14:25.900
including Tricia McGillis, my website designer,
包括我的网站设计师Tricia McGillis,

300
00:14:25.924 --> 00:14:28.289
who's working with my wonderful daughter
她和我优秀的女儿一起工作，

301
00:14:28.313 --> 00:14:31.851
to take my website and turn it into something
把我的网站打造成不可思议的地方，

302
00:14:31.875 --> 00:14:33.766
where all I have to do is write a blog.
在那儿我只需要写写博客。

303
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:36.286
I don't have to use the executive brain function ...
我不需要用大脑执行功能...

304
00:14:36.310 --> 00:14:39.889
Ha, ha, ha, I win!
哈哈哈，我赚到了！

305
00:14:39.913 --> 00:14:41.012
(Laughter)
（笑声）

306
00:14:40.988 --> 00:14:43.646
And I am so grateful to you.
同时我也非常感激你们。

307
00:14:44.673 --> 00:14:47.193
I don't want to say "the audience,"
我不想说，“ 观众们，“

308
00:14:47.217 --> 00:14:51.622
because I don't really see it as we're two separate things.
因为我不认为我们有什么不同。

309
00:14:51.646 --> 00:14:57.271
I think of it in terms of quantum physics, again.
再用量子物理学来说，

310
00:14:57.821 --> 00:15:03.118
And, you know, quantum physicists are not exactly sure what happens
你知道的，量子物理学不完全确定

311
00:15:03.142 --> 00:15:05.740
when the wave becomes a particle.
当波成为了质子时到底发生了什么。

312
00:15:05.764 --> 00:15:07.303
There are different theories --
有不同的理论——

313
00:15:07.327 --> 00:15:08.948
the collapse of the wave function,
波函数的瓦解，

314
00:15:08.972 --> 00:15:10.123
decoherence --
去相干性——

315
00:15:09.463 --> 00:15:11.839
but they're all agreed on one thing:
但它们都在一件事上达成共识：

316
00:15:11.887 --> 00:15:14.956
that reality comes into being through an interaction.
现实通过相互作用而存在的。

317
00:15:18.228 --> 00:15:19.641
(Voice breaking) So do you.
（嗓音低沉）你们也是。

318
00:15:20.448 --> 00:15:22.788
And every audience I've ever had,
所有我曾经或现在，

319
00:15:22.812 --> 00:15:24.366
past and present.
遇到的你们。

320
00:15:25.328 --> 00:15:29.309
Thank you so much for making my life real.
非常感谢，是你们使我的生命变得真实。

321
00:15:29.333 --> 00:15:30.445
(Applause)
（掌声）

322
00:15:30.469 --> 00:15:31.620
Thank you.
谢谢。

323
00:15:31.644 --> 00:15:33.104
(Applause)
（掌声）

324
00:15:33.128 --> 00:15:34.297
Thank you.
谢谢。

325
00:15:34.321 --> 00:15:35.374
(Applause)
（掌声）

326
00:15:35.398 --> 00:15:36.557
Thank you.
谢谢。

327
00:15:36.581 --> 00:15:37.606
(Applause)
（掌声）

328
00:15:37.630 --> 00:15:38.811
Thank you.
谢谢。